Quote:  hori n. (R) derogatory name used by some pakehas for a Maori. [M form of George]
Notes:  [nf. 1982 Collins Concise Eng. Dict.; 1985 Collins NZ Compact Dict. 236]



Date:  0/0/1988
Source:  Dictionary of Kiwi Slang, A
Author:
Vol / Page:  58
Edition:
Quote:  hori mildly derogatory term for a Maori, usually a male one; literally Maori transcription of `George', one of a number of excuses offered a few years ago to explain the use of the word in Parliament, without however cutting any ice.
